cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless networks and relay nodes. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the benefits of deploying a second relay and investigates the arrival and service rates of the queues. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper considers the stability conditions of the system. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention multimedia, but it does discuss throughput per user. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) is another less likely category as the paper evaluates the performance of the system, but it is not the main focus of the paper.
